  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Treatment care of end-stage renal insufficiency is an important public health issue. The
      balance between patients waiting for a kidney transplant and available graft raises
      questions. Because of the non-adherence, risk of graft loss is increased to 7 times so in
      this trial patients will experiment an educational therapy's program as soon as they
      register on the transplant list.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
